# Installing SASS in your local environment

To be able to install the Node.js package for Sass one has to ensure that node.js is already installed. To achieve this run the following command in the CLI

```CLI
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash
```

Exit the command line with the ***exit*** command and reopen the terminal.  
Install SASS usng the command below.  

```CLI
npm install sass -v 3.7.4
```
